claim.claim-text:
1. Fluid head height and either of foam and gas level control apparatus at a primary reaction chamber of an effluent processing electrocoagulation assembly, said apparatus comprising:
a first opening and an array of second openings in an upper portion of the primary chamber;
at least a first slidable cover located at said first opening, said cover including an orifice communicating with said opening, height of said orifice in the chamber being selectable by sliding said cover;
a plurality of second slidable covers each located at a different one of said second openings, said second covers each including an orifice communicating with a related one of said array of second openings, height of said orifices being selectable by sliding said covers; and
a first movable restrictor mounted on said first slidable cover for selective restriction of flow through said orifice of said first slidable cover.

11. Fluid head height and either of foam and gas level control apparatus at a primary reaction chamber of an effluent processing electrocoagulation assembly and having an upper portion, said apparatus comprising:
first and second openings in the upper portion of the primary reactor chamber;
first means movable in said first opening and having a fluid transfer orifice communicating with said opening for selectively positioning said orifice in said opening;
second means movable in said second opening, said second means including a fluid transfer orifice therein communicating with said second opening, said second means for selectively positioning said orifice therein in said second opening; and
first and second movable restrictors mounted on said first means and said second means, respectively, for selectively adjusting orifice area thereby selectively restricting flow through said orifices.
